ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How did you watch the videos? On my phone
How did you watch the videos? On my tablet
How did you watch the videos? On my computer
About how many times each week did you watch the videos (other than during your home visit)?
Please rate how comfortable you were using technology to watch the videos.
Notes: 0= Not at all comfortable; 10= Extremely comfortable

ElementDescription: How easy was it for you to watch the videos each week?
Notes: 0= Neither easy nor difficult; 1= Slightly easy; 2= Moderately easy; 3= Very easy; -3= Very difficult; -2= Moderately difficult; -1= Slight difficult

ElementDescription: What would have made it easier for you to watch the videos each week?
How did you feel about the pace of the videos?
Notes: 0= They were the right pace; 1= They were a little too slow; 2= There were way too slow; -1= They were a little too fast; -2= They were too fast

ElementDescription: How did you feel about the length of the videos?
Notes: 0= I though they were the right length; 1= I wish they were a little longer; 2= I wish they were a lot longer; -1= I wish they were a little shorter; -2= I wish they were a lot shorter

ElementDescription: How useful were the videos and handouts in helping you do pleasant activities?
Notes: 0= Not useful or useless; 1= Slight Useful; 2= Moderately Useful; 3= Very Useful; -1= Slightly Useless; -2= Moderately Useless; -3= Very Useless

ElementDescription: How useful were the videos and handouts in helping you change your unhealthy thoughts into healthier ones?
Notes: 0= Not useful or useless; 1= Slight Useful; 2= Moderately Useful; 3= Very Useful; -1= Slightly Useless; -2= Moderately Useless; -3= Very Useless

ElementDescription: How useful were the videos and handouts in helping you increase your positive social connections with other people?
Notes: 0= Not useful or useless; 1= Slight Useful; 2= Moderately Useful; 3= Very Useful; -1= Slightly Useless; -2= Moderately Useless; -3= Very Useless

ElementDescription: What would have made the videos and handouts more useful for you?
How did you feel about when the videos were shown to you during your home visit?
Notes: 1= I like that they were shown after we talked about parenting; 2= I wish they were shown before we talked about parenting; 3= Other

ElementDescription: Please specify other:
How well do you think the videos went along with what you talked about with your parent coach during your home visits?
Notes: 0= They did not go together well at all; 10= They went together really well

ElementDescription: What would have helped the videos and the home visits go together better?
What did you like most about the videos?
What did you like least about the videos?
What recommendations do you have to make the videos better?
When did you prefer watching the videos?
When did you prefer watching the videos?
Notes: 1=At the beginning of the home visit; 2=At the end of the home visit; 3=At a separate visit from our ABC session; 4=When I could view them on my own time; 5=Other
